      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "7a40f907-a520-40a8-9432-1499763257f5"],
     "\[LineSeparator]solves the Lindblad equation associated with the \
Hamiltonia ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      StyleBox["ham", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "8a8e891e-45e0-4c11-8260-f7b37a7894f2"],
     " and a set of quantum jump operators ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      StyleBox["jmp", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "866c6452-0dca-42a5-9c37-450dafb5aa99"],
     " for the initial condition ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      StyleBox["in", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "c6885a98-af97-4cf6-82dd-a4476806d128"],
     ", and returns the single-particle Green's function matrices at times \
from ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
       StyleBox["i", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "edda0087-06b1-4f62-88a7-83adc2d3ca40"],
     " to ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      SubscriptBox[
       StyleBox["t", "TI"], 
       StyleBox["f", "TI"]]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "f4b011f1-b9d8-47a3-8c5b-767e035603d5"],
     " at step ",
     Cell[BoxData[
      StyleBox["dt", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
      FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
      "a7d5ca9d-4603-4c84-888b-3697d6014be9"],
     "."
    }],ExpressionUUID->"88835fd4-5b14-4f0e-9d9a-f47121ff1fa3"]},
   {"", Cell[TextData[{
     Cell[BoxData[
      RowBox[{
       TemplateBox[{
